30|$|In {{this section}} we analyze the {{completeness}} of our proposed authentication protocol using <b>belief</b> <b>logic.</b> Burrows, Abadi, and Needham (BAN) logic [59] {{is the fundamental}} and popular <b>belief</b> <b>logic</b> which is widely used to analyse the completeness of various authentication schemes, but this logic has some shortcomings [60]. Gong, Needham, and Yahalom (GNY) logic [61] is the extended version of the BAN logic. We used GNY logic [61] to analyze our multi-factor authentication protocol. First, we describe important terminologies that we use in our <b>belief</b> <b>logic</b> and we re-describe our approach according to the GNY logic. Next, we analyze our goals and finally we report assumptions list.|$|E
