40|$|Cryptographic {{protocol}} design demands careful verification {{during all}} phases of development. <b>Belief</b> <b>logics,</b> {{in the tradition of}} the Burrows, Abadi, and Needham (BAN) logic of authentication [BAN 90], provide a simple, intuitive model, and allow natural expressions of a protocol and its goals. Since manual deduction is error-prone, protocol designers need automated tools to make effective use of these logics. Such tools often require excessive human intervention or supply inadequate feedback during the verification process...|$|R
